{
  "doc_id": "27762",
  "text": "Regional osteopenia can be induced in the anatomic region of interest in several ways. These can be classified as flap or flapless approaches, corticotomy, medullary osteotomy or both, and cortical incisions with use of burs or piezo instruments [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Most of these procedures have produced promising results suggesting increase in rate of OTM from 1.5 to 3 times [CITATION_5] . However, many of these procedures require additional surgeries, substantial increase in costs and increased morbidity [CITATION_6] .",
